post.body:
@nofish , some Chinese users reported that their ZeroNet fails to start after a self-update, which means the installation of ZeroNet is completely broken. I guess GFW sometimes interrupts the download, causing bad zip file. Extracting it and overwriting exiting source code will be a disaster! So more robust self-update is needed:
* ZipFile.testzip() should be used to Read all the files in the archive and check their CRC’s and file headers.
* rename src to src_bak instead of just overwriting it. The same to `plugins` `tools` folder.

